{
  "children":[
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Used to express uncertainty or possibility."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Word Breakdown"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许 combines concepts of inclusion and permission to express possibility."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"align":[],"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Component"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Meaning"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Also, too - expressing inclusion or possibility"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"许"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"tableCell"},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Allow, permit - words (言) + midday (午) = clear speech"}],"type":"tableCell"}],"type":"tableRow"}],"type":"table"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The combination suggests \"also allowing\" or \"including the possibility that,\" creating uncertainty\nrather than certainty."}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core Meaning & Usage"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许 represents "},{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"acknowledgment of uncertainty and alternative possibilities"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":". It's used:"}],"type":"paragraph"},
    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Uncertain predictions"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 也许会下雨 (yěxǔ huì xiàyǔ) - \"it might rain\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Polite suggestions"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 也许你是对的 (yěxǔ nǐ shì duì de) - \"perhaps you're right\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hypothetical scenarios"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 也许明天 (yěxǔ míngtiān) - \"maybe tomorrow\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Gentle disagreement"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":": 也许不是 (yěxǔ bù shì) - \"maybe not\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":true,"spread":false,"start":1,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Examples"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许吧"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yěxǔ ba) - \"maybe; perhaps\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许是"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yěxǔ shì) - \"maybe it is\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许不会"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yěxǔ bù huì) - \"perhaps not; maybe won't\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许可以"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yěxǔ kěyǐ) - \"perhaps possible\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"},{"checked":null,"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许有道理"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","value":" (yěxǔ yǒu dàolǐ) - \"perhaps there's some logic to it\""}],"type":"paragraph"}],"spread":false,"type":"listItem"}],"ordered":false,"spread":false,"start":null,"type":"list"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"也许 reflects Chinese cultural values of humility and avoiding absolute claims. In Chinese\ncommunication, expressing uncertainty shows wisdom and respect for complexity. It allows for\nface-saving when predictions prove wrong and demonstrates intellectual humility. The concept aligns\nwith Daoist philosophy that embraces uncertainty and change as natural parts of existence.\nUsing 也许 shows cultural sophistication by acknowledging that knowledge is limited and future\noutcomes are uncertain, making it an important marker of polite, thoughtful discourse."}],"type":"paragraph"}
